The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, June 11: India, Pakistan and Iran are likely to sign an agreement for a tri-nation gas pipeline costing over $7 billion by the end of next month, petroleum secretary M.S. Srinivasan said today. India and Pakistan will have a meeting shortly to sort out issues on transportation tariff and transit fee, he said.

 New Delhi, June 11: Firdose Vandrevala, Motorolas India chairman and corporate vice-president, has resigned from the company with effect from July 1 to pursue other interests. 

 Mumbai, June 11: Faced with a shortage of infrastructure in the country, the government is planning to allow setting up of airports on private land. 

 Mumbai, June 11: The rupee today strengthened by 34 paise to 40.80 against the dollar, largely because of capital inflows through the IPO route. 

 Mumbai, June 11: Carborundum Universal will acquire an 84.14 per cent stake in Russias Volzhsky Abrasives Works for an undisclosed amount.




